Oh, it's coming in.

81
00:04:51,658 --> 00:04:53,326
<i>Maya Sizitzy is at the scene!</i>

82
00:04:53,326 --> 00:04:54,161
<i>Hello, Maya!</i>

83
00:04:54,161 --> 00:04:56,563
<i>Hello, this is Maya Sizitzy</i>
<i>at the scene.</i>

84
00:04:56,563 --> 00:04:58,832
<i>It appears that the mysterious</i>
<i>giant organism</i>

85
00:04:58,832 --> 00:05:00,700
<i>that appeared at Oedo Hot Spa</i>

86
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,435
<i>has destroyed the facilities</i>
<i>in the area</i>

87
00:05:02,435 --> 00:05:04,004
<i>over the course</i>
<i>of the last several hours,</i>

88
00:05:04,004 --> 00:05:05,605
<i>only to mysteriously disappear.</i>

89
00:05:05,605 --> 00:05:08,875
Hey, hey, another mysterious alien
got out of the Sky Terminal again.

90
00:05:08,875 --> 00:05:10,410
There have been
quite a few recently.

91
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:11,411
Come on, guys!

92
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:13,079
Right now, whats more
important than the alien

93
00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:15,015
is how we're going
to manage our finances.

94
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:17,517
‐What?
‐What?

95
00:05:17,517 --> 00:05:18,718
That old hag!

96
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:23,390
If it's about the money, I already told
you I don't have any, you rotten hag!

97
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:28,295
What's that?

98
00:05:31,631 --> 00:05:32,699
Hey, chief!

99
00:05:32,699 --> 00:05:33,700
What's your problem?

100
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,001
What do you think you're doing?

101
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,469
Sorry about that,
my mistake.

102
00:05:36,469 --> 00:05:37,971
I'll come back another time.

103
00:05:38,405 --> 00:05:39,439
Hold it!

104
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:44,945
You're the Odd Jobs man, right?

105
00:05:44,945 --> 00:05:46,580
That's why you're coming with us.

106
00:05:47,581 --> 00:05:48,848
Sorry to disappoint you guys,

107
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:52,185
but my mother always told me
that it's not wise to follow strangers.

108
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:56,122
Didn't she also teach you that
it was not wise to disobey the law?

109
00:05:56,556 --> 00:05:58,391
You're with the government?

110
00:05:58,792 --> 00:06:00,594
We are with
the Immigration Bureau,

111
00:06:00,594 --> 00:06:04,297
and we came here to hire you
for a job, Mr. Odd Jobs.

112
00:06:08,935 --> 00:06:11,805
<i>When you say Taizo Hasegawa</i>
<i>of the Immigration Bureau,</i>

113
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:13,874
<i>you're talking about that big</i>
<i>shot government official</i>

114
00:06:13,874 --> 00:06:15,976
<i>who oversees all</i>
<i>Amanto immigration?</i>

115
00:06:15,976 --> 00:06:16,876
A big shot?

116
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,678
Does that mean he has
a big schlong?

117
00:06:18,678 --> 00:06:20,213
He's got an enormous one.

118
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:22,215
No, it means he is
an important person.

119
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:24,084
And you know, Kagura,

120
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:27,020
you really shouldn't be saying
such things like that in a show.

121
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:30,457
At any rate, what do you think a
government bigwig wants with us?

122
00:06:30,924 --> 00:06:33,093
What do you want with us,
Mr. Big Schlong?

123
00:06:33,093 --> 00:06:34,828
Odd Jobs Gin, was it?

124
00:06:35,128 --> 00:06:37,063
I heard there were some people
who would do anything

125
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:38,598
as long as I paid
the right price.

126
00:06:38,598 --> 00:06:40,567
So, I've come to ask you
to do a job.

127
00:06:41,868 --> 00:06:43,270
Do a job for you?

128
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:45,372
I didn't know you guys
even worked at all.

129
00:06:45,705 --> 00:06:46,873
Look around town man,

130
00:06:46,873 --> 00:06:49,276
because the Amanto are doing
whatever they please.

131
00:06:50,844 --> 00:06:52,279
That's pretty harsh, man.

132
00:06:52,545 --> 00:06:54,781
We're doing everything we can
these days, you know.

133
00:07:12,465 --> 00:07:16,636
Besides, the Capital has developed this
far primarily thanks to those aliens.

134
00:07:17,137 --> 00:07:20,407
<i>On top of that, they really seem</i>
<i>to like this place.</i>

135
00:07:20,573 --> 00:07:22,242
<i>We can't be reckless.</i>

136
00:07:22,942 --> 00:07:26,613
<i>The Amanto already have their networks</i>
<i>rooted in the heart of the government.</i>

137
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:30,684
<i>So it's best to stop dreaming about</i>
<i>driving them off of the Earth one day.</i>

138
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:38,124
The only option we have left is to try to
coexist with them to protect our kind.

139
00:07:40,593 --> 00:07:42,095
Coexist, eh?

140
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:45,265
And do you honestly enjoy
doing your job?

141
00:07:49,936 --> 00:07:51,271
Well, never mind.

142
00:07:51,371 --> 00:07:53,273
So, what do you want us
to do then?

143
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:57,644
Uh? Well, it's a job that
we can't carry out in the open.

144
00:07:58,078 --> 00:08:00,747
If it becomes public,
the government will lose face.

145
00:08:01,681 --> 00:08:04,684
The fact is that the government is
currently in a diplomatic crisis

146
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:08,321
that could have a decisive influence
on the future of our entire country.

147
00:08:09,189 --> 00:08:12,192
<i>Prince Hata from theo Midland Star</i>
<i>is staying in the Capital.</i>

148
00:08:12,425 --> 00:08:14,994
<i>And the prince happens</i>
<i>to have a small problem.</i>

149
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:20,600
My precious pet, my dear Pesu, seems
to have disappeared somewhere.

150
00:08:21,101 --> 00:08:23,403
Might I ask you
to collect him for me?

151
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:28,475
Hey, hold on you three!

152
00:08:29,976 --> 00:08:31,578
You guys are
the Odd Jobs right?

153
00:08:31,578 --> 00:08:33,313
You're supposed to do
anything, right?

154
00:08:33,446 --> 00:08:35,382
No, I know!
I know how you feel!

155
00:08:35,548 --> 00:08:37,250
But take the job, please!

156
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:40,286
Shut up or I'll break your shades,
you ugly government dirt bag.

157
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:42,522
And I'll yank off
your sad little beard.

158
00:08:42,689 --> 00:08:44,858
Fine, you can break my glasses,
yank off my beard,

159
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:46,126
but just take the job!

160
00:08:46,292 --> 00:08:47,927
We're seriously in trouble here.

161
00:08:47,927 --> 00:08:50,330
Our government borrowed quite
a bit of money from his country,

162
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:51,631
if you catch my drift.

163
00:08:51,631 --> 00:08:52,766
Why would I care about that?

164
00:08:52,766 --> 00:08:53,833
It's your problem.

165
00:08:53,967 --> 00:08:56,169
If this country's going to collapse
because of a mere pet,

166
00:08:56,169 --> 00:08:57,370
then, it should collapse then.

167
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,872
What do you mean by
a "mere pet"?

168
00:08:58,872 --> 00:09:01,141
Pesu is like a member
of the family.

169
00:09:01,274 --> 00:09:03,910
Then, please look for
your pet yourself, Prince Kaka.

170
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:07,247
Hey! It’s Prince Hata, not Prince Kaka!

171
00:09:07,514 --> 00:09:09,382
You should forget those
who walk out on you,

172
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:10,984
and prepare for a new love.

173
00:09:10,984 --> 00:09:13,553
That's what an independent woman
of this day and age would do.

174
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:14,254
Listen to me!

175
00:09:14,254 --> 00:09:15,889
He wasn't dumped,
and he isn't a woman!

176
00:09:15,989 --> 00:09:18,057
He may be a pinhead,
but he's still a prince!

177
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:19,159
‐He's still a prince!
‐Yes he's a pinhead...

178
00:09:19,159 --> 00:09:20,693
...but he's still a prince, right?

179
00:09:20,693 --> 00:09:22,462
That's right.
A pinhead, but still a prince!

180
00:09:22,462 --> 00:09:23,196
I get it.

181
00:09:23,196 --> 00:09:24,931
A pinhead, but still a prince, eh?

182
00:09:24,931 --> 00:09:26,966
So like I said,
he's a pinhead prince.

183
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:27,967
Listen to me!

184
00:09:27,967 --> 00:09:29,769
He's a pinhead,
but he's still a prince.

185
00:09:29,903 --> 00:09:30,737
You peasants!

186
00:09:30,737 --> 00:09:33,306
It's disrespectful to call
the Pinhead Prince a pinhead!

187
00:09:33,506 --> 00:09:35,842
But you just called me
a pinhead as well.

188
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:38,645
Can't you handle a problem
like this all by yourselves?

189
00:09:38,645 --> 00:09:40,213
Why hire us?

190
00:09:41,214 --> 00:09:43,817
Well, the thing is, we have
our reasons for needing help,

191
00:09:44,617 --> 00:09:48,121
but we also figured it would be
right up Mr. Odd Jobs' alley.

192
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:50,323
No, we may be called Odd Jobs,

193
00:09:50,323 --> 00:09:52,225
but we haven't lost
sight of ourselves

194
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:55,862
to the point where we would wag
our tails for the government officials

195
00:09:55,862 --> 00:09:57,497
and do their errands for them.

196
00:09:58,398 --> 00:10:00,066
Let's go, Shinpachi,
Kagura.

197
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:02,335
See ya, Big Schlong.

198
00:10:07,373 --> 00:10:11,744
Just so you three know, we intended
to compensate you very generously.

199
00:10:12,412 --> 00:10:13,880
Well then, what do we
have to do?

200
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:16,616
We are prepared to do
anything you say, master!

201
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:18,184
Talk about a quick transition?

202
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:19,886
You guys are such sellouts!

203
00:10:20,019 --> 00:10:23,623
What I want you to try to find is
this octopus like alien named Pesu.

204
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:26,259
It's probably wandering
around the city.

205
00:10:26,359 --> 00:10:29,562
I want you to capture it unharmed and
bring it back here before tomorrow.

206
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:38,838
Do you really think Pesu
would be in the harbor

207
00:10:38,838 --> 00:10:40,840
just because it looks
like an octopus?

208
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,175
It doesn't matter anyway.

209
00:10:42,175 --> 00:10:43,243
It can be anything.

210
00:10:43,243 --> 00:10:45,678
All we need is one hook,
and we can go from there.

211
00:10:45,678 --> 00:10:47,413
It’s like speed‐dating parties.

212
00:10:50,917 --> 00:10:52,986
Mm... octopus jars!

213
00:10:53,853 --> 00:10:56,890
You know fishermen set those up
and just wait for the octopus.

214
00:10:57,557 --> 00:11:00,260
Are you some emo teen
who can't confess his love?

215
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:03,630
